Thinking about St. Staniloae and how the main theme in Berserk is the concept of "causality", how the flow of cause and effect inevitably determines everything, with Skull Knight being fatalistic and resigned and Guts still trying to struggle against the flow of cause and effect.

Well St. Staniloae said man as a theomorphic being and all that also gets to somewhat stay outside the flow of causality (like God does) and make his own choices outside the chain of cause and effect in the world. So Guts basically has it right. Man is separate from "causation".
